entry.title: Who Are the Houthis and Why Is the U.S. Attacking Them?
entry.content: The Yemen-based rebel group has launched attacks on commercial ships bound for the Suez Canal, posing what could be one of the biggest threats to global shipping.

entry.title: The World's Smallest Soccer League Still Can't Find Enough Players
entry.content: Each year the red team and the black team of the Isles of Scilly Football League face off 20 times a season, battling it out for the league trophy.
